name: 45rpm
description:
45rpm's creative talents span graffiti art, illustration and graphic design. You may have seen his art on t-shirts for Fenchurch, Fracture skate decks and Becks Fusion iPhone cases. Having been a prolific street artist for over 10 years, his work has been showcased in numerous magazines and books, including the highly influential Street Sketchbook by Thames & Hudson.  Member of the infamous WHAT crew based in Bristol.

Strap Length: 260mm
Waterproof: 5ATM (50m)

Plastic case, polyurethane strap, stainless steel buckle and case back.

name: Dirty30
description:
Dirty Thirty has had a passion for art from an early age. That coupled with growing up surrounded by the graffiti scene of the mid 90s has led him to where he is today. Dirty Thirty's work has appeared in many exhibitions all over the world, as well as working with several clothing brands and record labels. Aside from galleries, his work can be found predominately in the street in the form of murals, paste ups and stickers. His trademark round face has now become a familiar and welcome sight to many in the UK and further afield!

name: Mr Penfold
description:
Amid the bicycle ridden streets of Cambridge Mr Penfold lurks. Observing characters, then re-creating them on walls and canvas’. Using strong linear elements against organic outlines with an overly scientific approach to colour, Penfold works with record labels, promoters and clothing companies and has also appeared in a range of magazines such as Graphotism, K Mag and Don’t Panic!

name: Rootz Artwork
description:
Rootz is an illustrator, artist and graphic designer.
He likes surfing, skateboarding, snowboarding and generally standing sideways. You’ll see that these loves have a huge influence on his work and he’s happiest when designing or illustrating graphics for surfboards and skateboards.
He likes black milk (guinness for the heathens among you) and listening to stoner rock, sludge, metal and punk. He’s worked as senior designer for a couple of different firms but is currently working & living in wet and windy North Devon freelancing and designing graphics for Bandit Skateboards, Escape Surfboards and the coolest thing in surfing ectic concepts.

name: Clumsy Kate
description:
Clumsy is a Designer, Illustrator, Artist, and Kustomiser, specialising in Kustom, Tattoo, Tiki, Rockabilly, Macabre and Cute. Her Work is inspired by her interests, which include the following:
Kustom car culture,
Tattoos,
Tiki,
Nauticalia,
Rockabilly (the style and the music),
Sock Monkeys,
